I check version 3.3.1 and 3.3.1.1 in both same issue.

After updating from eclipse 3.3 to 3.3.1(3.3.1.1) debug don't work.

I make small investigation and in class
org.eclipse.jdt.internal.launching.StandardVMType.java
I saw difference:
in old file
for(ListIterator liter = allLibs.listIterator(); liter.hasNext();) {
	lib = (LibraryLocation) liter.next();
	if(!set.add(lib.getSystemLibraryPath().toOSString())) {
		//did not add it, dupe
		liter.remove();
	}
}

in new file
for(ListIterator liter = allLibs.listIterator(); liter.hasNext();) {
	lib = (LibraryLocation) liter.next();
	IPath systemLibraryPath = lib.getSystemLibraryPath();
	String device = systemLibraryPath.getDevice();
	if (device != null) {
		// @see Bug 197866 - Installed JRE Wizard creates duplicate system libraries when drive letter is lower case
		systemLibraryPath = systemLibraryPath.setDevice(device.toUpperCase());
	}
	if(!set.add(systemLibraryPath.toOSString())) {
		//did not add it, duplicate
		liter.remove();
	}
}

I replace new class with old and can debug.

Additional info:
Before updating as I wrote earlier I add "\jre" in eclipse JRE Edit dialog in field jre home dirrectory. After that step debug work.
Use eclipse update and after updating debug won't work.
